  "verdict_tag": "DEATH",
  "verdict": "DEATH \u2014 amplification hypothesis FALSIFIED. frac_B does rise with \u03bb (up to 0.272 at \u03bb=2), exceeding 0.05, BUT: (i) the rise is driven by DISORDER, not order \u2014 G2 FAILS (disordered \u03bb=2 frac_B=0.272 \u226b baseline 0.0117); (ii) ferromagnetic ORDER SUPPRESSES it (\u03bb=2: disordered 0.272 > J_c 0.205 > 2J_c 0.099). The ordered condensate does NOT amplify E6c's curvature signal \u2014 it weakens it. What the coupling 'produces' is spacelike NOISE from incoherent orientation texture (any random internal field inflates b\u00b2); coherent (ordered) texture sweeps LESS internal area, so more order = less magnetic. The Meissner-style amplification is not realised.",
  "runtime_s": 36.011255979537964
}